      • processAlphabeticList

        public void processAlphabeticList(java.util.List<AlphabeticHeaders.AlphabeticItem> list)

        Processes the given alphabetic list. Whole list will be iterated and for each of its items will be checked the first char provided by AlphabeticHeaders.AlphabeticItem.getName(), so created headers data set will contains all different first characters founded at the first positions of obtained names.

        Also, the adapter, to which is this module attached, will be notified about data set change.

        Note, that the given cursor should be already sorted, otherwise the final headers data set can contains duplicates.

        Parameters:
        list - An alphabetic list to process.
        See Also:
        processAlphabeticCursor(android.database.Cursor)

      • processAlphabeticItem

        Process the given alphabetic item and creates header item from it if its first character from its name is different from the last processed one.

        Parameters:

        position - Position of the given item form the adapter's data set.
